name: (1S)-1,7,7-Trimethylbicyclo[2.2.1]heptan-2-one
Reason: To predict the melting point of (1S)-1,7,7-Trimethylbicyclo[2.2.1]heptan-2-one we look at the effects of the different functional groups and structural features. As a basic bicyclic structure, its base melting point is influenced by strong intermolecular forces due to rigidity and Van der Waals interactions, assumed to be around 100. The ketone group typically raises the melting point due to polar carbonyl groups encouraging dipole-dipole interactions, which we can estimate as +50. The presence of three methyl groups increases the molecular weight and the surface area, which can further enhance Van der Waals interactions; each group can be estimated to contribute an additional +10. Therefore, the predicted melting point increase due to the presence of these functional groups would be estimated as the sum of the effects.
